      "id": "r1",
      "order": 0,
      "text": "Plants and animals all need air. Only about one fifth of the air is oxygen. The other four fifths is another gas, without taste, smell or color, named nitrogen. Both plants and ani- mals need nitrogen as well as oxygen but they cannot take it from the air themselves. How do they get their supply of nitrogen?",
